products.name: Fender Player Stratocastor HSS
products.desc: Over the decades, players have been continually inspired by the sound of a Strat. From the clarity of the high end, through the gut punch of the mids and the solid lows, it's a sound that's helped define what an electric guitar should be—versatile enough for any style and broad enough for any player to find an individual voice. This Player Series Stratocaster puts all of the classic features of the Strat at your fingertips while adding a modern edge, including a bridge position humbucker and Floyd Rose double-locking tremolo system for a little more rock-and-roll attitude. With a solid alder body, a 22-fret maple fingerboard with a contemporary 9.5' radius for easy bending and the dive-bombing madness of a Floyd Rose, this Player Series Stratocaster HSS is primed and ready to carry you along your musical voyage.

products.name: Squier Bullet Stratocaster
products.desc: A great guitar for first-time and early beginning players who want classic tones in an easy-to-play electric guitar that's incredibly affordable. From the comfortable, slim, C-profile neck to the trio of Strat single-coil pickups, the Bullet Strat delivers that iconic Fender sound. The hardtail bridge delivers excellent sustain and, along with the die-cast tuning machines, seriously stable tuning. Case sold separately.

products.name: Ibanez AZ2402
products.desc: The AZ series carries with it all of the hallmarks of these tried and tested Ibanez qualities: the smooth oval neck profile, the well balanced asymmetrical body shape, and the neck heel allowing unrivaled playability an upper fret access. It also features a new tremolo bridge, as well as newly developed Hyperion pickups, produced in collaboration with Seymour Duncan. All of these elements help the AZ push the existing boundaries of playability and sound to the next level for modern cutting-edge players, while also providing a touch of classic styling.

products.name: Yamaha Pacifica 112VM
products.desc: The Yamaha Pacifica 112VM guitar combines renowned Yamaha build quality and playability with superb tone, and is available in four fashionable colors—including the Gray and Ice Blue finishes. The combination of a humbucking bridge pickup and two single-coil pickups provides a wide range of tonal possibilities, while the Alnico V pickups deliver warmth, clarity, and dynamic responsiveness. An alder body, a bolt-on maple neck with maple fretboard, a push-pull coil-split switch for additional tonal options, and a vintage-style tremolo bridge with heavy block saddles complement this beautiful and versatile instrument.

products.name: Gibson Custom Historic '57 Les Paul Goldtop
products.desc: This 2018 Historic Series recreations exemplifies Gibson Custom Shop's tireless quest for exacting accuracy to the original year of production, from the woods to the construction to the parts and precise contours throughout. Two new updates for 2018 include the inclusion of all True-Historic-spec parts and, for the first time, narrow/tall frets which bring the tone and playability closer to the character of the originals. Includes hardshell case.

products.name: Fender American Performer Telecaster RW
products.desc: With the American Performer Series, Fender brings players a line of affordable U.S.-made instruments loaded with stunning finishes, refined electronics and hardware and a few hidden surprises. These guitars and basses are designed for musicians of any level who seek Made in USA quality and playability at a surprisingly accessible price. The American Performer Telecaster HS with rosewood fingerboard takes the quintessential 'workhorse' guitar to a whole new level.

products.name: Epiphone Masterbilt Hummingbird
products.desc: Perhaps the rarest Epiphone model ever made, only 141 Excellente acoustic guitars were produced between 1963 and 1970. The Epiphone Excellente was made famous by country music legend Loretta Lynn and now joins the new Epiphone Masterbilt Collection. It features a solid Sitka spruce top, an ebony fingerboard with historical Pearl Cloud inlay, bone nut and saddle, and gold Kluson Waffleback tuners. The Epiphone Masterbilt Excellente is powered by the Fishman Sonitone Onboard Preamp System.

products.name: Cort AD810 OP Dreadnought
products.desc: Cort’s oldest acoustic series, the Standard Series, which now includes the AD810 OP dreadnought acoustic guitar, defines superb performance and value for the money. The Standard Series guitars are affordable, but offer good solid performance for beginners and hobbyists alike in a variety of models with different types of features for any playing situation.

products.name: Gibson SG Tribute
products.desc: Gibson's SG Standard Tribute bears the signature traits of the iconic double-cutaway solid-body, but with a few key updates. The traditional mahogany body is wed to a lively maple neck with 22-fret rosewood fingerboard, to deliver a ton that's a combination of bright and sweet, with plenty of sustain. Gibson's Alnico II 490 humbuckers are slightly overwound to deliver a modern edge that mellows back to a traditional PAF-style tone with a lighter touch or a slight rollback of the volume knob. Add it all together and get an SG that combines old and new for an amazing playing experience.

products.name: Jackson JS Series Dinky Arch Top
products.desc: This stylish 7-string features a 26.5” scale length for better low-end articulation, a lightweight and resonant poplar body with an arched top and a bolt-on maple neck with graphite reinforcement and scarf joint for rock-solid stability. Hosting 24 jumbo frets and piranha tooth inlays, the bound 12”-16” compound radius rosewood fingerboard creates the ideal playing surface for fat riffs and easy chording near the black plastic nut while gradually flattening in the upper registers for lightning-quick solos and wide bends without fear of fretting out.

products.name: Fender Squier Classic Vibe 60s Telecaster
products.desc: The Squier Classic Vibe ‘60s Telecaster Thinline electric guitar is a nod to the early semi-hollow Tele models from the 1960s, offering a distinctive classic sound at an affordable price.

products.name: Epiphone Les Paul Studio
products.desc: The Epiphone Les Paul Studio IG proves that a lightweight electric can punch above its class. Gibson’s original model made its debut in 1983. Essentially a Les Paul with less flash, it was designed for studio musicians who were primarily concerned with sound and playability. The Studio IG, however, leaves nothing to be desired. It’s got the tones and the looks to wow in any arena.

products.name: Epiphone Les Paul Standard '50s
products.desc: The Epiphone Les Paul Standard ’50s model electric guitar takes its stylistic and sonic cues from the iconic instrument first released in 1958. As part of Epiphone’s “Inspired by Gibson” collection, it features a mahogany body topped with AAA flame maple, dual ProBuckers, a long tenon set neck and more. It’s ideal for players looking for old-school design and classic sounds in a guitar with equal vibe and value.

products.name: Fender Squier Classic Vibe 50s Telecaster
products.desc: A great guitar for first-time and early beginning players who want classic tones in an easy-to-play electric guitar that's incredibly affordable. products.name: Fender Vintera 60s Stratocaster
products.desc: For players who want the style and sound of Fender’s golden era, they created the Vintera ‘60s Stratocaster. Equipped with the coveted features that defined the decade—including period-accurate neck profile and playing feel, along with re-voiced pickups—this guitar has all of the chime and articulation that made the Stratocaster a legend.

products.name: Yamaha Pacifica 612VIIX Solid Body
products.desc: The Yamaha Pacifica 612VIIX guitar recalls the Pacifica series’ LA custom shop roots with a combination of quality, playability and premium components. Equipped with Seymour Duncan Custom 5 TB-14 and SSL-1 single-coil pickups, the Pacific 612VIIX delivers warm and powerful sounds that you are in full control of via a 5-position pickup selector and a push-pull coil-split switch. Additional features include Grover locking tuners, a Wilkinson VS50 bridge along with a Graph Tech TUSQ nut and string trees to ensure optimal performance and exceptional tuning stability.

products.name: Fender American Original ‘60s Stratocaster
products.desc: As the world changed in the '60s, the Strat changed, too. It mellowed out with a smooth rosewood fretboard and the look of a mint green pickguard, but still maintained its clarity of voice. The American Original '60s Stratocaster captures that original vibe and adds a modern 9.5' radius to accommodate the desires of modern players. Loaded with period-correct and vintage-style pickups and hardware, it's like a time machine with extra-plush seating.

products.name: Gibson Les Paul Tribute
products.desc: Gibson's Les Paul Tribute brings you all the vibe and feel of a traditional Les Paul, in a ultra-modern-weight-relieved mahogany body. An easy-to-play rounded profile on a set-in maple neck with rosewood fingerboard adds a hint of brightness, and the Alnico II 490 humbuckers deliver loads of power and sustain for those classic Les Paul tones.

products.desc: The '57 Les Paul Custom VOS electric guitar is perhaps the most beautiful guitar ever made, revered both for its undeniable upscale aesthetic and its versatile sound. The dark, dense ebony fingerboard produces clarity and sustain while the single-piece solid mahogany body adds a warmth and mid-range unlike any other Les Paul.

products.desc: The Fender '65 Deluxe Reverb Combo Amp has a sound big enough to cut through the muddiest mix, but it's small enough to turn up make the most of natural tube distortion in small clubs. This makes it the perfect studio amp, as well. It's a resurrection of a classic vintage tone monster, and its current iteration is used by many big-name bands, such as Flogging Molly, O.A.R. and Maroon 5. Crank up this faithful, U.S.-made reissue for your daily requirement of fat Fender tone. Delivers 22W through a 12' speaker. Features two channels (normal, vibrato), all-tube circuitry, tube vibrato, tube spring reverb, Blackface cosmetics and two-button footswitch to control the reverb and vibrato effects.

products.name: Fender Bassbreaker 30R 30W
products.desc: Ripping a page from the supercharged high-gain distortion and spacious reverb of the popular Fender Bassbreaker 15, the 30-watt Bassbreaker 30R adds full channel-switching capability to allow for precise, individual control over your clean and distorted tones—while the built-in effects loop offers yet another dose of custom-tailored personality to your sound. Boasting a single 12” Celestion V-Type speaker, this easily portable combo amp packs quite the punch of distinctively crunchy Bassbreaker tone.

products.name: Fender 65 Twin Reverb
products.desc: The Fender '65 Twin Reverb Amp is an authentic all-tube reproduction of the original classic! It has earned a reputation of being one of the cleanest tube amps ever, but it delivers a taste of the trademark Fender crunch when cranked up high. Delivers 85W through two Jensen 12' speakers. It has two channels, tube vibrato, tube spring reverb, tilt-back legs and Blackface cosmetics. Includes two-button footswitch to control reverb and vibrato effects. Order the optional Fender amp cover to protect your investment (see accessory box on this page).

More portable than the AC15 and more powerful than the AC4, the combo features the classic Top Boost tone circuit that provides an array of classic and modern tones. Now equipped with reverb and a master volume, it is the perfect companion for the home, studio or stage. The Top Boost tone can be further adjusted via Gain, Bass, Treble, Reverb and Volume controls. The combo is equipped with two 12AX7 and one EL84 tube, and a 10” Celestion VX10 speaker. Dimensions: 520 x 210 x 410 mm. Weight: 12.3 kg.

Boasting both a Normal and Top Boost channel, the AC15 Custom is an all-tube, EL84 driven workhorse that delivers 15 watts of authentic British tone into your choice of a genuine Celestion Greenback speaker. The AC15 Custom also offers footswitchable spring reverb and classic VOX tremolo to enhance the already impressive sound. Adored by the biggest names in music for nearly 60 years, the VOX AC15 Custom carries on the tradition that began in 1958 and offers guitarists the unmistakable sound of VOX, with all the refinements of a modern amplifier. Vox have re-released many of their acclaimed series amplifiers in a limited edition colour, offering you an individual look. Featuring a new Limited Edition White Bronco look. Vox’s long tradition of limited edition custom colour amps have been extremely popular amongst Vox players for decades, due to their uniqueness and tonal abilities. products.name: Marshall Studio Vintage SV20C
products.desc: The SV20C is an all valve handbuilt amp designed and built in the UK, to accurately recreate the classic Marshall tone. The SV20C combines the raw power of the 1959SLP and authentic voice of classic rock in a new portable style. The amp that first defined rock ‘n’ roll in the 60s has been revised for the present day, whilst remaining faithful to the original with its Plexi design and all-valve tone. Still considered a classic by scores of legendary guitarists, the SV20C lets you play like your heroes on stage, in the studio and at home. Portable and adaptable, the Studio Vintage Combo is suitable for the home with the option to switch between 20W and 5W at any time.

Real valve tone with the organic warmth and response, adjustable power level, compact cabinet with a Celestion Ten-30 speaker for both portability and projection. The amplifier has 2 channels with classic gain and ultra gain for instant sound switching capability, alongside a versatile range of EQ controls (improved for 2018) that let you fully sculpt your sound, bass switch that complements a resonant bass boost, Softube emulated direct output - you can plug the output directly into a mixing desk or recording device and access a high-quality emulation. Ideal for no-fuss recording or for sending a direct signal to your front-of-house mixing desk. Serial FX Loop, Controls: Classic Gain: Gain/Volume, Ultra Gain: Gain/Volume, Tone Shift, Treble, Middle, Bass, Deep, Reverb. Footswitch included.

products.name: Marshall DSL1CR
products.desc: Tube guitar combo Amp. The combo is equipped with an 8” Celestion Eight-15 speaker chosen for its ability to deliver exceptional tone at lower volumes. The DSL features two foot switchable channels: CLASSIC GAIN and ULTRA GAIN. The CLASSIC GAIN channel delivers sparkling clean sounds through to the more aggressive break-up of a Marshall JCM800 amplifier. The ULTRA GAIN channel provides even more distortion and break-up for players looking for higher gain tone from their amplifier. Both channels share a passive three-band EQ, with BASS, MIDDLE and TREBLE controls. The EQ section also features Tone Shift, which when activated reconfigures the pre-amp mid frequencies making DSL ideal for contemporary metal tones, especially when combined with higher gain settings. The DSL 1 features professional quality digital REVERB and a series FX LOOP, giving you rich valve tone at an ear-friendly volume. Footswitch included.

products.name: Orange Crush 20RT
products.desc: 2-channel transistor guitar combo from Crush series offering typical Orange sound. It features a 3-band EQ, pre-amplifier with high gain and sensitive overdrive, detailed tone saturation or distorted channel, similar to that of the iconic Rockerverb combo in the transistorized form. Combo offers the power of 20 W and is equipped with one 8' Voice of the World speaker. In addition, it is equipped with a built-in reverb, tuner, or Cabsim function that simulates massive tone of Orange 4 x 12 cabinet through the headphone output. It´s operated by Dirty Gain, Treble, Middle, Bass, Clean/Dirty Volume and Reverb potentiometers, channel switch or tuner switch. Combo has built-in a 1/4' instrument input, headphone output, AUX input or the footswitch input (not included). Dimensions: 375 x 325 x 197 mm, weight: 7.2 kg.

products.name: Orange CR60C Crush
products.desc: 1 x 12', 60W Combo Guitar Amplifier with Digital Reverbs, and Effects Loop. Orange Amplifiers expands its line of solid-state Crush amps with new CR60C 60-watt 1 x 12' Combo. This Crush amp delivers more authentic Orange tone than ever, with both amp channels being designed after the Rockerverb. The clean channel sports two gain stages that start to break up when it's cranked, and the dirty channel uses four gain stages to deliver classic Orange overdrive tones.

products.name: Boss Katana 212 Cabinet
products.desc: Speaker cabinet for the Boss Katana amplifier head. The versatile Katana Cabinet 212 is a companion cabinet for the popular Katana-Head guitar amplifier. BOSS’s special design provides enhanced bass response and rugged durability while keeping the weight down for easy mobility. The cabinet comes loaded with two custom 12-inch speakers that deliver powerful, punchy sound with rich, full bottom end, offering exceptional performance for tones from super-clean to ultra-heavy. And with the detachable back panel section, you can easily go from a tight and focused closed-back stack tone to the spacious open-back sound of a classic combo.

products.name: Boss Nextone Artist
products.desc: Electric guitar combo amplifier. Combining classic tube sound and feel with next-generation tonal diversity, the BOSS Nextone series presents an exciting new concept in professional guitar amplification. Distinctive channel voicings deliver a wide range of inspiring tones, while four selectable Class AB analog power amp types provide instant access to the unique characteristics of 6V6, 6L6, EL84, and EL34 output tube sections. Backed by our advanced Tube Logic approach, each power amp type re-voices the entire circuit from input to output, putting the complete sonic experience of these signature power stages in one amp for the very first time. Connect to the Nextone Editor and become a virtual tech, fine-tuning bias, sag, EQ, and other internal settings to perfectly match your individual style and touch. Nextone also includes convenient modern features for stage playing, such as built-in effects, a line out for mic-free direct tone, and a power control for expressive cranked-amp sound at manageable volumes. And thanks to Tube Logic, you get to enjoy all the great sound and response of your favorite tube designs without the backbreaking weight and ongoing maintenance hassles.

products.name: Vox PATHFINDER 10
products.desc: Compact solid-state all-analog 10-watt guitar combo amplifier from Pathfinder series with classical Vox design that includes basket-weave, leather-look, distinctive diamond grille cloth and chicken head knobs. It is equipped with 6.5” VOX Bulldog speaker and Gain, Treble, Bass, Volume control knobs and Clean/Overdrive switch. Amplifier provides connectivity via instrument jack input and phones/line jack output. Dimensions: 380 x 260 x 170 mm. Weight: 4.8 kg.

products.name: Fender Frontman 10G
products.desc: For the beginning electric guitarist or anyone who wants a small, easy-to-use practice amp with quality tone and a great price, the Frontman 10G is at your service. Conveniently compact and built with classic Fender style, it delivers full sound from its 6' speaker, with a gain control and overdrive switch that rock guitar tones from tube-emulated overdrive to full-strength ultra-saturated distortion—perfect for blues, metal and famous Fender clean tone.

products.name: Fender Champion 50XL
products.desc: Digital guitar combo from Fender Champion series in limited edition. Featuring a range of built-in amp models and 12 effects classic effects built in ranging from reverb and delay to vibraphone and 4 built-in stompbox effects including compressor, overdrive, distortion and octaver. The Fender Champion 50XL amp boasts a generous 50-Watt output via a well-appointed 12-inch custom Celestion 'Midnight 60' speaker, which delivers your tone with absolute clarity. There are two channels at your disposal consisting of Blackface clean and one with selectable amp voices. The Blackface clean tone produces that legendary jangly sound with cutting mid to high energy. The switchable amp voices allow you to tweak your amp's character to suit a plethora of musical styles from jazz to metal, country to punk, and everywhere in-between. Optional 2-button footswitch for channel selection and effect toggling / footswitch not included, TAP button to match the song’s tempo, 3,5 mm stereo auxiliary input for jamming with media player, 3,5 mm stereo headphone output for silent practice. Dimensions (H x W x D): 438 x 438 x 229 mm. Weight: 8,6 kg. Colour: Black.

products.name: Fender Champion 20
products.desc: Versatile 20-watt combo guitar amplifier from Champion series that delivers a selection of warm tones perfect for practising and performing for beginners and slightly advanced players. Solid-state design features one channel with Selectable Amp Voice that allows for dial-in of specific amp voices to suit the style of the player. Amplifier is equipped with one 8” Fender Special Design speaker, and a wide range of effects including reverb, chorus, flanger, delay, Vibratone and more, with dedicated Tap Tempo button. Other controls include Gain, Volume, Voice, Treble, Bass, FX Level, and FX Select. It also features one instrument 1/4' input, 1/8' aux input for external media device, and 1/8' headphone output. Amplifier delivers classic Fender Blackface styling with silver grill and sturdy handle. Dimensions: 325 x 350 x 190 mm. Weight: 5.4 kg.

products.name: Fender Champion 40
products.desc: Versatile 2-channel 40-watt combo guitar amplifier from Champion series that delivers a selection of warm tones perfect for practising and performing for beginners and slightly advanced players. Solid-state design features two channels, Blackface Clean and a Selectable Amp Voice that allows for dial-in of specific amp voices to suit the style of the player. Amplifier is equipped with one 12” Fender Special Design speaker, and a wide range of effects including reverb, chorus, flanger, delay, Vibratone and more, with dedicated Tap Tempo button. Other controls include Gain, Volume 1 and 2, Voice, Treble, Bass, FX Level, and FX Select. It also features one instrument 1/4' input, 1/8' aux input for external media device, and 1/8” headphone output. Amplifier deliver classic Fender Blackface styling with silver grill and sturdy handle. Dimensions: 438 x 229 x 438 mm. Weight: 8.6 kg.

products.name: Fender Champion 100
products.desc: Versatile 2-channel 100-watt combo guitar amplifier from Champion series that delivers a selection of warm tones perfect for practising and performing for beginners and slightly advanced players. Solid-state design features two channels with Selectable Amp Voice that allows for dial-in of specific amp voices to suit the style of the player. Amplifier is equipped with two 12” Fender Special Design speaker, and a wide range of effects including reverb, chorus, flanger, delay/echo, Vibratone and more, with dedicated Tap Tempo button. Other controls include Gain, Volume, Voice, Treble, Bass, FX Level, and FX Select. It also features one instrument 1/4' input, 1/8” aux input for external media device, and 1/8” headphone output. Amplifier delivers classic Fender Blackface styling with silver grill and sturdy handle. 2-button footswitch pedal is included. Dimensions: 260 x 660 x 490 mm. Weight: 18.2 kg.
